parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure with Internal Water Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: no leaks of coolant or oil

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: AWD system failure can cause loss of traction, difficulty driving in rain or snowy weather, and potentially lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and traction control system failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Transfer case failure can cause loss of power, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. It can also cause a burning smell and smoke in the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Pump Failure Causing Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause coolant to leak into the engine, leading to catastrophic engine damage, overheating, and potentially leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of power, steering, and braking, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on
and rattling noises are heard from the engine. In some cases
there are no warning signs before the failure.
